SYMMETRIC BINARY TREE

You are given a binary tree. Your task is to determine whether the tree is symmetric, meaning it is a mirror reflection of itself around its center.

FUNCTION DESCRIPTION

Function name: isSymmetric

This function checks whether a binary tree is symmetric.

PARAMETERS

root
The root node of the binary tree

RETURN VALUE

Return true if the binary tree is symmetric
Return false otherwise

CONSTRAINTS

1 ≤ number of nodes ≤ 1000
-100 ≤ Node value ≤ 100

INPUT FORMAT

The first line contains an integer T, the number of test cases

For each test case:
The first line contains an integer N
The second line contains N space-separated values representing the tree in level order
Use null or -1 to represent missing nodes

OUTPUT FORMAT

For each test case, print:
true if the tree is symmetric
false otherwise

SAMPLE INPUT

2
7
1 2 2 null 5 5 null
7
1 2 2 null 3 null 4

SAMPLE OUTPUT

true
false

EXPLANATION

In the first test case
The left and right subtrees are mirror images, so the tree is symmetric

In the second test case
The structure is not a mirror image, so the tree is not symmetric


class Solution {
    public boolean isSymmetric(TreeNode root) {
      if(root==null)  return true;
      return isMirror(root.left,root.right);
      
}private boolean isMirror(TreeNode a,TreeNode b){
    if(a==null&&b==null) {
        return true;
    }
    if(a==null||b==null) {
        return false;
    }if(a.val!=b.val) return false;
    return isMirror(a.left,b.right)&&
    isMirror(a.right,b.left);
}}
